3\\u0647\\u0648\\u0644\\u0629 \\u062a\\u062a\\u0628\\u0639 \\u0645\\u0633\\u0627\\u0647\\u0645\\u0627\\u062a\\u0647\\u0645 \\u0648\\u0645\\u0639\\u0631\\u0641\\u0629 \\u0643\\u064a\\u0641\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0633\\u062a\\u062e\\u062f\\u0627\\u0645 \\u0623\\u0645\\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0645. \\u062a\\u0648\\u0641\\u0631 \\u0645\\u0639\\u0638\\u0645 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0646\\u0635\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0625\\u0644\\u0643\\u062a\\u0631\\u0648\\u0646\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0630\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0633\\u0645\\u0639\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0637\\u064a\\u0628\\u0629 \\u062a\\u0642\\u0627\\u0631\\u064a\\u0631 \\u0645\\u0641\\u0635\\u0644\\u0629 \\u0639\\u0646 \\u062a\\u0623\\u062b\\u064a\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062a\\u0628\\u0631\\u0639\\u0627\\u062a\\u060c \\u0645\\u0645\\u0627 \\u064a\\u0633\\u0645\\u062d \\u0644\\u0644\\u0645\\u0627\\u0646\\u062d\\u064a\\u0646 \\u0628\\u0645\\u0634\\u0627\\u0647\\u062f\\u0629 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u062a\\u0627\\u0626\\u062c \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0644\\u0645\\u0648\\u0633\\u0629 \\u0644\\u062f\\u0639\\u0645\\u0647\\u0645. \\u062a\\u0639\\u0645\\u0644 \\u0647\\u0630\\u0647 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0634\\u0641\\u0627\\u0641\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u062a\\u0639\\u0632\\u064a\\u0632 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062b\\u0642\\u0629 \\u0641\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0646\\u0638\\u0645\\u0627\\u062a \\u0627\\u0644\\u062e\\u064a\\u0631\\u064a\\u0629\\u060c \\u0645\\u0645\\u0627 \\u064a\\u0634\\u062c\\u0639 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0632\\u064a\\u062f \\u0645\\u0646 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u0627\\u0633 \\u0639\\u0644\\u0649 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u0634\\u0627\\u0631\\u0643\\u0629.<\\/p>"}}}','image' => 'aed27724-5f45-4601-9efe-6dd589ed3a19.webp','status' => '1','created_at' => '2023-11-04 16:52:40','updated_at' => '2023-11-04 16:52:40'),
            array('id' => '9','admin_id' => '1','title' => '{"language":{"en":{"title":"You Can Give Poor In India...Clean Water & Food"},"es":{"title":"Usted puede dar a los pobres en la India... agua limpia y alimentos"},"ar":{"title":"\\u064a\\u0645\\u0643\\u0646\\u0643 \\u0627\\u0644\\u062a\\u0628\\u0631\\u0639 \\u0644\\u0644\\u0641\\u0642\\u0631\\u0627\\u0621 \\u0641\\u064a \\u0627\\u0644\\u0647\\u0646\\u062f...\\u0627\\u0644\\u0645\\u064a\\u0627\\u0647 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0646\\u0638\\u064a\\u0641\\u0629 \\u0648\\u0627\\u0644\\u063a\\u0630\\u0627\\u0621"}}}','slug' => 'you-can-give-poor-in-indiaclean-water-food','our_goal' => '28000.00','raised' => '0.00','to_go' => '28000.00','desc' => '{"language":{"en":{"desc":"<p>Providing clean water and food to the poor in India is an urgent and essential humanitarian endeavor. India, a country of over 1.3 billion people, is home to a significant portion of the world\'s impoverished population. While India has made remarkable progress in various sectors, including technology and economic growth, it still faces immense challenges in ensuring access to clean water and sufficient food for all its citizens.<\\/p><p>The issue of clean water is particularly pressing in India. While there have been improvements in recent years, a significant portion of the population lacks access to safe and clean drinking water. This lack of access can lead to numerous health problems, including waterborne diseases such as cholera and diarrhea. In rural areas, women and children often spend hours each day collecting water from distant sources, leaving little time for education or other productive activities.<\\/p><p>The provision of clean water is not only a matter of health but also a question of dignity and human rights. Every individual, regardless of their socioeconomic status, deserves access to clean water. Addressing this issue requires a multifaceted approach, including the construction of water infrastructure, education about hygiene practices, and awareness campaigns about water conservation.<\\/p><p>Simultaneously, the problem of hunger persists in India. While the country produces an abundance of food, the distribution and access to this resource remain unequal. Millions of people, especially in rural areas, suffer from chronic food insecurity. Malnutrition, particularly among children, remains a major concern, affecting their physical and cognitive development.<\\/p><p>To alleviate these problems, various initiatives and organizations are working tirelessly to provide food assistance to those in need. Government-run programs such as the Public Distribution System (PDS) offer subsidized food grains to low-income households. NGOs and community-based organizations also play a significant role in distributing food to the underprivileged.<\\/p>"},"es":{"desc":"<p>Proporcionar agua potable y alimentos a los pobres de la India es una tarea humanitaria urgente y esencial. India, un pa\\u00eds de m\\u00e1s de 1.300 millones de habitantes, alberga a una parte importante de la poblaci\\u00f3n empobrecida del mundo. Si bien la India ha logrado avances notables en varios sectores, incluidos la tecnolog\\u00eda y el crecimiento econ\\u00f3mico, todav\\u00eda enfrenta inmensos desaf\\u00edos para garantizar el acceso al agua potable y a alimentos suficientes para todos sus ciudadanos.<\\/p><p>La cuesti\\u00f3n del agua potable es particularmente apremiante en la India. Si bien ha habido mejoras en los \\u00faltimos a\\u00f1os, una parte importante de la poblaci\\u00f3n carece de acceso a agua potable segura y limpia. Esta falta de acceso puede provocar numerosos problemas de salud, incluidas enfermedades transmitidas por el agua como el c\\u00f3lera y la diarrea. En las zonas rurales, las mujeres y los ni\\u00f1os suelen pasar horas cada d\\u00eda recogiendo agua de fuentes distantes, dejando poco tiempo para la educaci\\u00f3n u otras actividades productivas.<\\/p><p>El suministro de agua potable no es s\\u00f3lo una cuesti\\u00f3n de salud sino tambi\\u00e9n una cuesti\\u00f3n de dignidad y derechos humanos. Cada individuo, independientemente de su estatus socioecon\\u00f3mico, merece acceso al agua potable. Abordar esta cuesti\\u00f3n requiere un enfoque multifac\\u00e9tico, que incluya la construcci\\u00f3n de infraestructura h\\u00eddrica, educaci\\u00f3n sobre pr\\u00e1cticas de higiene y campa\\u00f1as de concientizaci\\u00f3n sobre la conservaci\\u00f3n del agua.<\\/p><p>Al mismo tiempo, el problema del hambre persiste en la India. Si bien el pa\\u00eds produce abundantes alimentos, la distribuci\\u00f3n y el acceso a este recurso siguen siendo desiguales. Millones de personas, especialmente en las zonas rurales, sufren de inseguridad alimentaria cr\\u00f3nica. La desnutrici\\u00f3n, especialmente entre los ni\\u00f1os, sigue siendo una preocupaci\\u00f3n importante que afecta su desarrollo f\\u00edsico y cognitivo.<\\/p><p>Para paliar estos problemas, diversas iniciativas y organizaciones est\\u00e1n trabajando incansablemente para proporcionar asistencia alimentaria a quienes la necesitan. Los programas administrados por el gobierno, como el Sistema de Distribuci\\u00f3n P\\u00fablica (PDS), ofrecen cereales alimentarios subsidiados a hogares de bajos ingresos. Las ONG y las organizaciones comunitarias tambi\\u00e9n desempe\\u00f1an un papel importante en la distribuci\\u00f3n de alimentos a los desfavorecidos.<\\/p><p>Un aspecto crucial para abordar la inseguridad alimentaria no es s\\u00f3lo brindar ayuda inmediata sino tambi\\u00e9n garantizar la sostenibilidad alimentaria a largo plazo. Esto se puede lograr mediante el desarrollo agr\\u00edcola, la mejora de las pr\\u00e1cticas agr\\u00edcolas y la mejora de las redes de almacenamiento y distribuci\\u00f3n de alimentos. Los esfuerzos para reducir el desperdicio de alimentos y promover pr\\u00e1cticas agr\\u00edcolas sostenibles pueden contribuir en gran medida a abordar el problema<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p>"},"